# Marital Satisfaction Data Mining Project

## Overview
This project performs data mining on the Marital Satisfaction Questionnaire dataset 
covering 7,000+ respondents across 33 countries, to uncover patterns of marital 
satisfaction across different cultures.

## Files
- Data_Mining_Project(log).ipynb — main project notebook
- Marital satisfaction_Data.xlsx — raw dataset
- Marital.csv / Cleaning2.csv — cleaned datasets
- MaritalCleaning.ipynb — data preprocessing notebook

## How to Run
### Option 1 — Google Colab (Recommended)
Open the original notebook directly: [paste your Colab link here]

### Option 2 — Local
1. Clone or download this repository
2. Make sure the dataset files are in the same folder as the notebook
3. Install dependencies: pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn imbalanced-learn
4. Open Data_Mining_Project(log).ipynb in Jupyter Notebook or VS Code

## Project Steps
1. Data Preprocessing & Cleaning
2. Exploratory Data Analysis
3. Feature Engineering (feature construction, selection, dimensionality reduction)
4. Model Building — Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Naïve Bayes, KNN, LDA
5. Class Imbalance Handling — SMOTE, Undersampling, SMOTE+Tomek
6. Model Evaluation & Interpretation

## Key Finding
Self-esteem and love-related features were identified as the strongest predictors 
of marital satisfaction across cultures. Best model: Logistic Regression (F1: 0.498).
